Module  : Format Edit Notification
Version : 1.0.2
Author  : Maurice Makaay <maurice@phorum.org>

This module can be used to change the formatting of the message edit
notification (e.g. use less space between the body and notification,
use a smaller font, etc.)

This can be done by defining an HTML prefix and postfix in the
module's settings.


Install:
--------

- Unpack the archive;

- Move the directory "format_edit_notification" to the directory "mods"
  within your Phorum installation;

- Login as administrator in Phorum's administrative interface and
  go to the "Modules" section;

- Enable the module "Format Edit Notification".

- Go into the settings for the module and tweak the prefix and postfix
  to your needs and taste.


Example prefix/postfix combinations:
------------------------------------

- Put less space between the message body and the notification:

  -> prefix   <br/><br/>
  -> postfix  *** empty ***

- Keep standard space, but use a smaller font:

  -> prefix   <br/><br/><br/><small>
  -> postfix  </small>

- Put the notificaton in a <div> (CSS code can define the styling):

  -> prefix   <div class="edit_notification">
  -> postfix  </div>

- Do some full styling in a <div> around the notification:

  -> prefix   <div style="margin 10px 0px 10px 0px;
                          padding: 5px;
                          border: 2px solid black;
                          background-color: red;
                          color: white">
  -> postfix  </div>

